From: Sarveshwar Bandi <sarveshwarb@serverengines.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Jan 2010 05:15:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] be2net: ethtool self test reorganization.
References: bnc#556959
Git-commit: 8f47afe080df450eedda7b29873512c2a9a9adcb
Patch-mainline: v2.6.34-rc1

The ddr dma ethtool self test needs to be performed even when ETH_TEST_FL_OFFLINE is not set.

Signed-off-by: Sarveshwar Bandi <sarveshwarb@serverengines.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Brandon Philips <bphilips@suse.de>

---
 drivers/net/benet/be_ethtool.c |    7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

Index: linux-2.6.32-SLE11-SP1/drivers/net/benet/be_ethtool.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.32-SLE11-SP1.orig/drivers/net/benet/be_ethtool.c
+++ linux-2.6.32-SLE11-SP1/drivers/net/benet/be_ethtool.c
@@ -549,10 +549,11 @@ be_self_test(struct net_device *netdev,
 						&data[2]) != 0) {
 			test->flags |= ETH_TEST_FL_FAILED;
 		}
+	}
 
-		data[3] = be_test_ddr_dma(adapter);
-		if (data[3] != 0)
-			test->flags |= ETH_TEST_FL_FAILED;
+	if (be_test_ddr_dma(adapter) != 0) {
+		data[3] = 1;
+		test->flags |= ETH_TEST_FL_FAILED;
 	}
 
 	if (be_cmd_link_status_query(adapter, &link_up, &mac_speed,
